A 34-year-old woman has been arrested for allegedly killing a 45-year-old man believed to have been her boyfriend in Lulekani, outside Phalaborwa, Limpopo. Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says it’s alleged that the suspect used a blunt object to hit the deceased after the two had a fight on Friday night. Ngoepe says the suspect will appear in the Lulekani Magistrate’s Court on Monday. “The Police in Lulekani have arrested a 34-year-old woman for allegedly killing her 45-year-old boyfriend, following an alleged conflict between the two at Steve Biko section. The cause and motive behind this incident are not clear at this stage but domestic violence may not be ruled out. The suspect will appear before Lelekani magistrate’s court facing the charge of murder soon.”